{"product_id": "12180", "page": 7, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-19", "text": "Grand Theft Auto 2 took Grand Theft Auto classic concepts and made it better. Cars now have even more and better weapons. You weren\u2019t satisfied with just running over \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665es, hoes, and pedestrians in the prequel? You now can electrocute them with your electro gun. The radio is chock full of satire and hilarity. There are even more varied ways to earn cash and respect in the game. To top it all off, the graphics for Grand Theft Auto 2 is a massive upgrade from its predecessor. Everything is much more detailed which in turn makes the explosions and gores that much more satisfying. If you\u2019re going to play a classic Grand Theft Auto game, might as well start at number 2 and skip the first one entirely.", "hours": 17.5, "username": "amBADatgames", "products": 5168, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "12180", "page": 8, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-31", "text": "If you can get this game to work or part 1, they are totally a blast to play!  I remember the just running drugs, hitting up on gangs, and out running the cops!  Unfortunatley the new GTA games do not make you feel the same way this one did... the closest GTA to the original is San Andreas.\nBascially you meet people or answer the phone in this top down view mission based game but in a open world situation.", "username": "McMillanFixXxeR", "products": 414, "early_access": false}
